text: SBF's prepared testimony to the House Committee, which he never gave because he was arrested, is on the internet. He makes the case that the whole bankruptcy is a plot between Sulllivan and Crowwell and the trustee to make money, that he had funding all lined up and that Alameda

failed only because the value of its asset fell 90% among other bizarre things. Maybe it's the start of an insanity defense! @jimcramer @tomkeene @ferrotv @riskreversal @lisaabramowicz1 @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick @ScottWapnerCNBC @carlquintanilla
